  "texts": [
    "G-Retriever, which aggregates topological information as soft prompts, outperforms other retrievers, but it also fails to consider topology during the retrieval process.",
    "Our GRAG approach addresses this limitation by directly retrieving subgraphs instead of individual entities and incorporating topological information into the LLM during the generation phase, thereby achieving optimal performance on both datasets.",
    "We conducted a series of ablations to our GRAG framework to identify which components play a key role.",
    "We evaluate four model variants trained differently, where fine-tuning is used and 2-hop ego-graphs are retrieved in all settings: w/o Retrieval trains the LLM without retrieving subgraphs, instead providing the entire graph to the LLM.",
    "w/o Graph Encoder trains the LLM using the text on the retrieved textual subgraphs, but does not generate graph tokens to provide the graph context; w/o Soft Pruning indicates that irrelevant entities are not pruned when retrieved subgraphs are encoded to the graph tokens; w/o Graph Description trains the LLM without the hierarchical text descriptions of retrieved textual subgraphs."
  ],
